computeNodesAndEntitiesInContainer

public void computeNodesAndEntitiesInContainer(AbstractContainerNode node,
                                               java.util.List<AbstractNode> nodes,
                                               java.util.Collection<EntityIdentifier> entities)
                                        throws VINException
Description copied from class: AbstractGraphBuilderBean
From a node representing a container, provides all nodes in the container and all entities in the container. Please remark that nodes and entities are not representing exactly the same entities since: - some nodes have no entities - some entities may be in a container but have no node (example is paging, nodes for non displayed pages do not exist)

Overrides:
computeNodesAndEntitiesInContainer in class AbstractGraphBuilderBean
Parameters:
node - The node for the container
nodes - Output parameter, the computed list of nodes in the container, can be null if not desired
entities - Output parameter, the computed collection of entities in the container, can be null if not desired. The collection insertion order matters: in some cases, it is used to insert entities in the good order in the basket. This is the default implementation. We use the CollectionModel to build the nodes and entities. It should be changed by derived class for efficiency or correctness (default implementation will not work with container paging for example).
Throws:
VINException
